801
00:50:39.985 --> 00:50:41.253
On the beach. tomorrow.

802
00:50:41.277 --> 00:50:42.570
I'm Will Cage.
you're Dr. Carter.

803
00:50:42.570 --> 00:50:45.490
We've had this conversation before.
You have two fingers behind your back.

804
00:50:45.614 --> 00:50:46.782
I've had the visions.

805
00:50:47.034 --> 00:50:48.034
I've seen the Omega.

806
00:50:54.081 --> 00:50:57.103
It's... pretty much game over tomorrow.

807
00:50:57.126 --> 00:50:58.795
So can we move this along?

808
00:50:59.128 --> 00:51:00.130
Okay.

809
00:51:00.838 --> 00:51:01.840
Where?

810
00:51:02.673 --> 00:51:05.259
There's a dam.
it's in the mountains.

811
00:51:05.260 --> 00:51:06.260
I saw German writing.

812
00:51:06.677 --> 00:51:08.512
Do you think you can
work out where that is?

813
00:51:08.512 --> 00:51:08.563
Well. I mean there can't be
too many places that fit that

814
00:51:08.576 --> 00:51:08.637
description. Do you think you
can work out where that is?

815
00:51:08.639 --> 00:51:11.974
Well. I mean there can't be
too many places that fit that description.

816
00:51:11.974 --> 00:51:13.268
I'll see what I can do.

817
00:51:13.851 --> 00:51:14.936
Training's over.

818
00:51:15.311 --> 00:51:16.438
I'll see you tomorrow.

819
00:51:16.730 --> 00:51:19.398
- We don't even know where we're going.
- We will. soon enough.

820
00:51:20.192 --> 00:51:23.032
In the mean time. you need to figure out
a way to get us off that beach.

821
00:51:45.175 --> 00:51:47.092
What next? Where are we going?

822
00:51:47.094 --> 00:51:48.780
- Yeah...
- Which way? Focus!

823
00:51:48.804 --> 00:51:49.471
Which way?

824
00:51:49.472 --> 00:51:50.552
I'm thinking. I'm thinking.

825
00:51:50.554 --> 00:51:52.514
Okay... Oh. man!

826
00:51:53.057 --> 00:51:54.434
How far do we make it?

827
00:51:54.643 --> 00:51:58.230
Well. it's... hard to say.

828
00:51:59.940 --> 00:52:02.108
Hold!

829
00:52:02.442 --> 00:52:03.442
Okay. go!

830
00:52:05.237 --> 00:52:06.362
Son of a bitch!

831
00:52:06.530 --> 00:52:08.447
- I thought stepping left. ducking.
- Fine.

832
00:52:08.447 --> 00:52:09.572
Just for the record. stepping left...

833
00:52:09.574 --> 00:52:11.815
- Stepping left. ducking right.
- It was pretty specific.

834
00:52:11.992 --> 00:52:14.246
Stepping left. ducking right.

835
00:52:14.788 --> 00:52:15.788
Move on.

836
00:52:18.833 --> 00:52:19.876
Hold on!

837
00:52:20.210 --> 00:52:23.213
Now remember. across the
trench. twelve o'clock.

838
00:52:23.380 --> 00:52:24.380
then look to your right.

839
00:52:31.554 --> 00:52:32.501
You're not being
specific. you understand?

840
00:52:32.514 --> 00:52:33.472
Oh. okay.

841
00:52:33.472 --> 00:52:36.059
You need to be specific.
otherwise I'm dead.

842
00:52:36.351 --> 00:52:37.351
Rita.

843
00:52:39.271 --> 00:52:40.271
Cage!

844
00:52:42.231 --> 00:52:44.315
That takes us up to the
top and then the trench.

845
00:52:44.317 --> 00:52:47.077
I'm gonna step left. there's gonna be
a Mimic there which I'll kill...

846
00:52:56.788 --> 00:52:59.373
There's an explosion. I'm gonna run
thirty paces to the north west.

847
00:52:59.373 --> 00:53:02.501
I'm gonna duck at the top of that trench.
and then I'm gonna turn left.

848
00:53:12.054 --> 00:53:13.472
I got something on my face?

849
00:53:16.099 --> 00:53:17.099
No!

850
00:53:25.025 --> 00:53:26.025
Cage!

851
00:53:26.360 --> 00:53:27.880
We've been looking everywhere for you!

852
00:53:29.028 --> 00:53:30.028
Cage!

853
00:53:32.134 --> 00:53:33.134
Guys.

854
00:53:33.157 --> 00:53:35.702
Guys can we just...

855
00:53:35.994 --> 00:53:37.829
not do this today?

856
00:53:38.079 --> 00:53:39.289
What are you talking about?

857
00:53:39.914 --> 00:53:42.708
Farell almost strung us up
by our bullocks for losing track of you!

858
00:53:45.086 --> 00:53:46.170
Okay. Skinner.

859
00:53:46.380 --> 00:53:47.380
Watch this.

860
00:53:48.632 --> 00:53:50.050
Now I'm gonna close my eyes.

861
00:53:50.800 --> 00:53:51.885
- Ready?
- Yeah.

862
00:53:59.934 --> 00:54:01.811
I didn't mind the extra push ups.

863
00:54:11.987 --> 00:54:13.239
It's a new day. people!

864
00:54:14.282 --> 00:54:15.534
Destiny calls.

865
00:54:15.951 --> 00:54:18.202
The world expects only one thing from us:

866
00:54:18.327 --> 00:54:19.329
That we will win!

867
00:54:34.969 --> 00:54:39.141
The current situation on the front line
show heavy casualties...

868
00:54:39.807 --> 00:54:42.128
It's about time we showed
those things what we're made of.

869
00:54:42.351 --> 00:54:44.688
My father flew in the battle of Britain.

870
00:54:44.938 --> 00:54:47.523
three years before the
yanks came into the war.

871
00:54:48.275 --> 00:54:51.193
Couldn't be broken. backbone.

872
00:54:51.360 --> 00:54:53.739
My Uncle George landed
on the beach of Normandy. yeah.

873
00:54:54.239 --> 00:54:57.701
In their day. this war
would have been over by now.

874
00:54:57.909 --> 00:54:59.536
What do they want with us anyway?

875
00:54:59.994 --> 00:55:01.621
It's obvious. isn't it?
Minerals.

876
00:55:01.746 --> 00:55:02.581
Minerals?

877
00:55:02.581 --> 00:55:04.061
- Yeah. minerals.
- Oxygen. they want.

878
00:55:04.416 --> 00:55:04.875
Oxygen?

879
00:55:04.875 --> 00:55:05.166
Think about it...

880
00:55:05.291 --> 00:55:06.452
What difference does it make?

881
00:55:07.376 --> 00:55:09.086
They're here. they're winning.

882
00:55:09.795 --> 00:55:12.340
And whatever it is. they're gonna get it.

883
00:55:12.840 --> 00:55:14.092
Shouldn't you be over there?

884
00:55:15.510 --> 00:55:16.510
I've been over there.

885
00:55:17.721 --> 00:55:19.056
More times than anybody.

886
00:55:19.889 --> 00:55:23.601
As a matter of fact.
I'm usually long dead by now.

887
00:55:26.563 --> 00:55:27.563
Coward.

888
00:55:31.025 --> 00:55:33.945
- What's going on?
- The power's gone.

889
00:56:42.222 --> 00:56:44.849
I found the Omega. I found it.
It has to be here.

890
00:56:45.182 --> 00:56:47.059
Großer Dam. Germany.
This as got to be it.

891
00:56:47.059 --> 00:56:48.144
It fits the description perfectly.

892
00:56:48.269 --> 00:56:49.646
Yes. you found it.

893
00:56:49.771 --> 00:56:50.771
Again.

894
00:56:51.356 --> 00:56:55.443
What difference does it make?
Cause we're never gonna get there.

895
00:56:56.318 --> 00:56:57.695
No matter what we do.

896
00:56:58.530 --> 00:57:00.990
no matter how carefully we plan.

897
00:57:01.949 --> 00:57:03.577
we can't get off that beach.

898
00:57:14.336 --> 00:57:16.882
You can do this. You can.

899
00:57:17.173 --> 00:57:20.052
You keep coming here everyday
and I'll train you.

900
00:57:23.221 --> 00:57:24.597
You already have.

901
00:57:44.159 --> 00:57:45.177
I'm waiting. Nance!

902
00:57:45.202 --> 00:57:47.036
Five hundred meters and closing fast!

903
00:57:48.288 --> 00:57:49.288
What the...?!

904
00:57:58.422 --> 00:57:59.422
Reloading.

905
00:58:11.353 --> 00:58:12.353
What's next?

906
00:58:14.523 --> 00:58:15.731
Straight shot.

907
00:58:16.315 --> 00:58:17.376
Up the hill.

908
00:58:17.400 --> 00:58:18.400
Okay.

909
00:58:19.235 --> 00:58:20.277
Hey. Serge.

910
00:58:20.445 --> 00:58:21.445
The new guy...

911
00:58:22.239 --> 00:58:23.532
what's his name again?

912
00:58:27.452 --> 00:58:29.829
We need a vehicle to get further inland.

913
00:58:30.288 --> 00:58:31.288
Then what's the problem?

914
00:58:31.289 --> 00:58:33.592
The problem is the ambush
waiting for us down

915
00:58:33.603 --> 00:58:35.918
there. they kill before
we find a working car.

916
00:58:36.128 --> 00:58:37.878
Okay. so what's the current plan?

917
00:58:38.255 --> 00:58:39.431
The two cars I haven't
tried are the Minivan...

918
00:58:39.443 --> 00:58:40.630
Yep.

919
00:58:40.632 --> 00:58:41.925
- And the green SUV.
- Okay.

920
00:58:42.925 --> 00:58:45.762
I'll head for the SUV. draw the
Mimics to me. You go for the Minivan.

921
00:58:45.887 --> 00:58:48.097
You get it started. just go. take off.

922
00:58:48.222 --> 00:58:49.932
- Do not wait for me.
- Okay.

923
00:58:51.768 --> 00:58:54.579
Well... just don't forget to disconnect
the caravan before you take off.

924
00:58:54.603 --> 00:58:55.856
You are going to be in a hurry.

925
00:58:56.063 --> 00:58:57.815
you don't want any dead weight.

926
00:59:23.215 --> 00:59:24.215
Come on.

927
00:59:39.315 --> 00:59:40.317
Come on. Cage!

928
00:59:46.907 --> 00:59:47.907
Can't see!

929
00:59:49.951 --> 00:59:51.036
Did you...?

930
00:59:59.920 --> 01:00:02.130
Stay where you are. remain calm.

931
01:00:02.755 --> 01:00:06.467
If you are in a vehicle.
please lock the doors and stay inside.

932
01:00:15.059 --> 01:00:17.103
The enemy has reached London.

933
01:00:17.228 --> 01:00:17.771
Repeat.

934
01:00:17.978 --> 01:00:19.898
London is under attack.

935
01:00:24.902 --> 01:00:25.987
That's good driving.

936
01:00:26.405 --> 01:00:28.280
I forgot to unhook the trailer.

937
01:01:14.119 --> 01:01:15.746
You don't talk much.

938
01:01:16.871 --> 01:01:17.956
Not a fan.

939
01:01:18.456 --> 01:01:19.456
Of talking?

940
01:01:20.000 --> 01:01:21.585
Not a fan of talking. no.

941
01:01:23.461 --> 01:01:25.338
You know. you eventually do talk to me.

942
01:01:27.757 --> 01:01:31.177
It's usually around Lyon. you tell me about
the time you went there with your family.

943
01:01:31.762 --> 01:01:33.262
Your brother got lost.

944
01:01:35.349 --> 01:01:37.224
I've never been to Lyon.

945
01:01:37.851 --> 01:01:39.518
You tell me your middle name.

946
01:01:41.103 --> 01:01:42.146
Peyton.

947
01:01:44.523 --> 01:01:45.733
That's not my middle name.

948
01:01:51.364 --> 01:01:53.492
You found your brother in
the arcade. by the way.

949
01:01:55.869 --> 01:01:58.246
Well maybe I made it all
up just to keep you quiet.

950
01:01:58.454 --> 01:01:59.454
But you do talk to me.

951
01:01:59.706 --> 01:02:01.726
Cage. I do not need to get to know you.

952
01:02:01.750 --> 01:02:05.021
And if you knew what was good for you.
you wouldn't want to get to know me either.

953
01:02:05.045 --> 01:02:07.047
It's the only way you make
it through this thing.

954
01:02:08.382 --> 01:02:10.342
What about Hendricks. you get to know him?

955
01:02:11.217 --> 01:02:12.344
How do you know that name?

956
01:02:12.469 --> 01:02:13.844
You mention him.

957
01:02:14.346 --> 01:02:15.472
That's not possible.

958
01:02:15.806 --> 01:02:17.764
- Then how do I know his name?
- When did I mention him?

959
01:02:17.766 --> 01:02:18.766
Under what circumstance?

960
01:02:20.976 --> 01:02:22.978
Is he why you won't talk to me?

961
01:02:26.692 --> 01:02:28.735
Don't ever mention his name again.

962
01:02:30.237 --> 01:02:31.445
Why...

963
01:02:31.445 --> 01:02:33.007
- are you in love with him?
- He's dead!

964
01:02:36.534 --> 01:02:38.411
And I watched him die three hundred times.

965
01:02:38.536 --> 01:02:42.289
and I remember... every detail.
I remember everything.

966
01:02:42.416 --> 01:02:44.458
So I don't need to talk about it.

967
01:02:49.755 --> 01:02:50.882
I'm sorry.

968
01:02:51.340 --> 01:02:52.342
It's just war.

969
01:03:55.947 --> 01:03:57.990
There's nothing here. keep going.

970
01:04:21.639 --> 01:04:22.932
We have to find the keys.

971
01:04:24.309 --> 01:04:25.559
Let's just siphon the gas.

972
01:04:25.686 --> 01:04:27.728
And why drive when we can fly?

973
01:04:28.438 --> 01:04:29.563
In that thing?

974
01:04:29.690 --> 01:04:31.525
Let me guess. you're afraid of heights.

975
01:04:31.650 --> 01:04:33.193
I'm afraid of crashing.

976
01:04:33.527 --> 01:04:35.027
I'm not at all ashamed to admit it.

977
01:04:35.152 --> 01:04:37.364
You'll be fine. Cage.
You'll learn.

978
01:04:39.157 --> 01:04:41.326
- What is it?
- It's nothing. I'm fine.

979
01:04:42.369 --> 01:04:43.704
- What is it?
- It's nothing.

980
01:04:44.286 --> 01:04:45.286
Rita.

981
01:04:49.126 --> 01:04:50.126
Let me see.

982
01:05:10.521 --> 01:05:12.481
We have to find the keys to the helicopter.

983
01:05:12.733 --> 01:05:14.293
I'm sure they're around here somewhere.

984
01:05:15.277 --> 01:05:16.945
You know the heli's full of fuel.

985
01:05:17.278 --> 01:05:18.655
I found a hose.

986
01:05:19.572 --> 01:05:20.782
We're flying. Cage.

987
01:05:25.202 --> 01:05:27.914
Well. let's just say we
find keys. you know?

988
01:05:28.706 --> 01:05:30.291
Get that helicopter started.

989
01:05:30.916 --> 01:05:32.878
We don't have our jackets or ammunition.

990
01:05:33.295 --> 01:05:35.088
And it's gonna be dark in a few hours.

991
01:05:37.798 --> 01:05:40.260
Might be better just going
back to the farmhouse.

992
01:05:40.635 --> 01:05:44.556
seeing what we could salvage.
You know. spend the night there.

993
01:05:45.097 --> 01:05:46.199
Come back here in the morning.

994
01:05:46.224 --> 01:05:49.101
And curl up by the fire
and open a bottle of wine?

995
01:05:52.981 --> 01:05:54.483
We should just reset.

996
01:05:55.400 --> 01:05:56.693
- It's a dead end.
- Hey. hold... just...

997
01:05:56.818 --> 01:05:57.938
If it's all the same to you.

998
01:05:58.152 --> 01:06:00.780
I'm tired. I'm in pain.
I'd rather just start fresh.

999
01:06:00.989 --> 01:06:03.449
I'll tell you what. take a few minutes.
Coffee's ready.

1000
01:06:04.034 --> 01:06:05.659
I'll look around for the
keys. that's productive.

1001
01:06:05.952 --> 01:06:06.952
Ten minutes.

1002
01:06:07.161 --> 01:06:07.621
Okay.

1003
01:06:07.871 --> 01:06:09.081
And then I'm killing you.

1004
01:06:09.998 --> 01:06:10.998
Fine.

1005
01:06:14.668 --> 01:06:16.128
I can't believe you found coffee.

1006
01:06:18.507 --> 01:06:19.507
Thank you.

1007
01:06:23.219 --> 01:06:24.219
Oh. Sugar. right?

1008
01:06:24.637 --> 01:06:25.637
Yeah.

1009
01:06:31.204 --> 01:06:32.204
Thank you.

1010
01:06:32.228 --> 01:06:33.230
Hold on. three.

1011
01:06:33.438 --> 01:06:34.438
You like three.

1012
01:06:48.202 --> 01:06:50.414
There's a shirt over there.
it should be your size.

1013
01:06:58.963 --> 01:07:00.798
How many times have we been here?

1014
01:07:07.347 --> 01:07:08.514
How many times?

1015
01:07:09.724 --> 01:07:10.934
Where are the keys?

1016
01:07:12.476 --> 01:07:13.956
- Where are the Goddamn keys?
- Okay.

1017
01:07:17.273 --> 01:07:18.983
You can fly it. can't you?

1018
01:07:19.150 --> 01:07:20.358
No. Well... yes.

1019
01:07:20.360 --> 01:07:23.320
I mean. I can take off.
I'm still working on my landing.

1020
01:07:23.320 --> 01:07:25.282
What are we still doing here?
You're wasting time!

1021
01:07:25.740 --> 01:07:26.240
Rita.

1022
01:07:26.242 --> 01:07:27.742
You start that engine. you die!

1023
01:07:31.913 --> 01:07:33.373
This is as far as you go.

1024
01:07:33.831 --> 01:07:35.166
No matter what I do.

1025
01:07:36.376 --> 01:07:38.128
This is as far as you ever make it.

1026
01:07:46.469 --> 01:07:49.306
There's a Mimic buried twenty yards away.

1027
01:07:49.806 --> 01:07:51.682
It attacks when you start the engine.

1028
01:07:53.226 --> 01:07:55.436
Get your weapon
and get in the helicopter. Cage.

1029
01:07:55.771 --> 01:07:57.563
There's more than a field battle there.

1030
01:08:00.192 --> 01:08:01.650
Only one of us ever makes it.

1031
01:08:01.860 --> 01:08:02.360
Get in.

1032
01:08:02.568 --> 01:08:03.954
The only thing we haven't
tried is a version where

1033
01:08:03.967 --> 01:08:05.364
you walk away. just go
back to the farmhouse.

1034
01:08:05.489 --> 01:08:08.824
There's food. you wait
there until I get back.

1035
01:08:08.949 --> 01:08:09.951
You'll be safe.

1036
01:08:10.077 --> 01:08:12.262
I'm a soldier. I volunteered.

1037
01:08:12.286 --> 01:08:13.288
I'm not walking away.

1038
01:08:13.413 --> 01:08:14.539
You die here!

1039
01:08:14.956 --> 01:08:15.956
Right here!

1040
01:08:18.167 --> 01:08:19.293
I...can't save you.

1041
01:08:19.961 --> 01:08:22.171
And if I go on and kill the Omega.

1042
01:08:22.338 --> 01:08:23.340
You're dead.

1043
01:08:23.881 --> 01:08:24.881
Forever.

1044
01:08:25.007 --> 01:08:26.885
Why does it matter what happens to me?

1045
01:08:30.889 --> 01:08:33.934
I wish I didn't know you.

1046
01:08:36.478 --> 01:08:37.478
But I do.

1047
01:10:08.904 --> 01:10:10.529
My middle name...

1048
01:10:11.782 --> 01:10:12.783
is Rose.

1049
01:10:33.345 --> 01:10:34.970
On your feet. maggot!

1050
01:10:46.483 --> 01:10:48.443
Looks there's hope for your. Private.

1051
01:10:48.568 --> 01:10:50.862
Hope in the form of glorious combat.

1052
01:10:51.697 --> 01:10:53.073
Battle is the great redeemer.

1053
01:10:53.323 --> 01:10:55.448
The fire and crucible
in which the only true heroes are forged.

1054
01:10:55.449 --> 01:10:56.451
The one place...

1055
01:11:08.421 --> 01:11:09.421
Yes?

1056
01:11:10.506 --> 01:11:12.134
Who said you could talk to me?

1057
01:11:16.095 --> 01:11:17.930
Do I have something on my face. soldier?

1058
01:11:21.643 --> 01:11:23.185
I'm sorry to disturb you. Sergeant.

1059
01:11:45.667 --> 01:11:48.186
Alright. man. Let's get this show
on the road. I gotta suite up.

1060
01:11:51.006 --> 01:11:52.173
Where's your helmet?

1061
01:11:53.884 --> 01:11:55.260
I'm not gonna wear one.

1062
01:11:55.719 --> 01:11:56.970
It's a distraction.

1063
01:11:59.390 --> 01:12:00.390
Have you been drinking?

1064
01:12:00.390 --> 01:12:03.077
I need three more clips of five-five-six.

1065
01:12:03.100 --> 01:12:05.561
eight grenades and an extra battery.

1066
01:12:09.733 --> 01:12:10.733
Get it!

1067
01:12:17.698 --> 01:12:18.698
Oy!

1068
01:12:18.699 --> 01:12:19.701
Oy. mate!

1069
01:12:20.827 --> 01:12:22.747
I think there's something
wrong with your suite!

1070
01:12:24.122 --> 01:12:25.457
There's a dead guy in it.

1071
01:12:26.582 --> 01:12:27.582
Yeah!

1072
01:12:27.833 --> 01:12:28.417
Wooh-hoo! We made it!

1073
01:12:28.418 --> 01:12:30.753
Thank God. we made it! Yeah...!

1074
01:14:33.377 --> 01:14:34.377
Finish it!

1075
01:15:29.015 --> 01:15:30.600
It isn't there.

1076
01:15:30.809 --> 01:15:32.309
What do you mean
the Omega isn't there?

1077
01:15:32.310 --> 01:15:33.704
My guess is it never was.

1078
01:15:33.729 --> 01:15:35.063
They knew we were coming.

1079
01:15:35.229 --> 01:15:37.606
They ambushed us.
The visions were a trap.

1080
01:15:39.150 --> 01:15:41.653
Just like Rita's visions
were a trap at Verdun.

1081
01:15:43.404 --> 01:15:44.966
It could have killed me. but it didn't.

1082
01:15:45.323 --> 01:15:46.323
It's after my blood.

1083
01:15:46.449 --> 01:15:47.993
So they know who you are. they...

1084
01:15:49.619 --> 01:15:50.619
They want their power back.

1085
01:15:50.621 --> 01:15:52.328
And they're gonna get
it one way or another.

1086
01:15:52.329 --> 01:15:54.248
unless we find the Omega.

1087
01:15:55.082 --> 01:15:56.542
There... there isn't any
other way. we're finished!

1088
01:15:56.667 --> 01:15:58.337
No. we're not finished.

1089
01:15:58.920 --> 01:16:00.148
It doesn't work.
I can't get it to work...

1090
01:16:00.171 --> 01:16:01.994
You built a prototype
at Whitehall.

1091
01:16:02.006 --> 01:16:03.841
Yes! And I got fired for
it. thank you very much.

1092
01:16:04.676 --> 01:16:06.344
- What is this thing. anyway?
- It's a transponder.

1093
01:16:06.345 --> 01:16:08.146
You stick it into the
Alpha and it taps into

1094
01:16:08.158 --> 01:16:09.971
the wavelength connecting
it to the Omega.

1095
01:16:09.972 --> 01:16:11.475
That's the idea anyway.

1096
01:16:11.807 --> 01:16:14.685
But I can't get it to work.
not with the equipment I have on hand.

1097
01:16:17.314 --> 01:16:18.623
How do we get you what you need?

1098
01:16:18.648 --> 01:16:19.981
Well. that's the thing. I mean...

1099
01:16:19.983 --> 01:16:22.985
when I was at Whitehall I built one.
I was even ready to test it.

1100
01:16:23.235 --> 01:16:24.653
but when I told my superiors about it.

1101
01:16:24.654 --> 01:16:25.654
well I lost my job.

1102
01:16:25.780 --> 01:16:27.365
They thought he was crazy.

1103
01:16:27.740 --> 01:16:29.368
So all we need to do is go to Whitehall.

1104
01:16:29.909 --> 01:16:32.371
He'd be arrested ten feet
from the front doors.

1105
01:16:32.496 --> 01:16:34.122
Psyche ward dissection. remember?

1106
01:16:35.247 --> 01:16:36.416
Hey. hey. hey! Aren't you
forgetting something?

1107
01:16:36.707 --> 01:16:39.418
The transponder requires
a live Alpha to make it work.

1108
01:16:39.543 --> 01:16:40.878
We don't need one.

1109
01:16:41.546 --> 01:16:43.131
We got the next best thing.

1110
01:16:46.510 --> 01:16:49.345
When the Chinese delegation comes out.
you pick up the pace.

1111
01:16:51.681 --> 01:16:54.350
There's a guy with a yellow arm band
that always recognizes you.

1112
01:16:54.475 --> 01:16:57.104
So just keep your head down
and stay to my right.

1113
01:17:03.902 --> 01:17:05.487
Nicely done.

1114
01:17:08.007 --> 01:17:09.007
One.

1115
01:17:09.032 --> 01:17:09.740
Two.

1116
01:17:09.949 --> 01:17:10.951
Hold.

1117
01:17:25.465 --> 01:17:26.465
Turn.

1118
01:17:27.009 --> 01:17:29.094
Okay. keep walking.
Just go straight ahead.

1119
01:17:30.804 --> 01:17:32.221
Robinson

1120
01:17:32.930 --> 01:17:34.617
I've asked not to be disturbed.

1121
01:17:34.640 --> 01:17:35.766
This had better be critical.

1122
01:17:36.018 --> 01:17:37.101
Fate of mankind.

1123
01:17:37.226 --> 01:17:38.310
Critical enough?

1124
01:17:39.061 --> 01:17:40.354
I don't believe what I'm seeing.

1125
01:17:40.479 --> 01:17:42.189
I've had more than my share of that.

1126
01:17:43.065 --> 01:17:45.109
Sit down. General.
and stay away from your desk.

1127
01:17:46.069 --> 01:17:48.195
I'd take her very seriously if I were you.

1128
01:17:50.032 --> 01:17:51.658
I have to hand it to you. Major.

1129
01:17:52.576 --> 01:17:55.243
When you left this office today.
I never imagined you'd be back.

1130
01:17:55.244 --> 01:17:57.372
let alone with my most decorated soldier.

1131
01:17:57.497 --> 01:17:58.932
I'm here to tell you a story. General.

1132
01:17:58.957 --> 01:18:02.292
And at first it's gonna sound ridiculous.
but the longer I talk the more rational.

1133
01:18:02.293 --> 01:18:03.170
it's going to appear.

1134
01:18:03.171 --> 01:18:04.671
Tell him you'll call back.

1135
01:18:04.898 --> 01:18:05.898
Tell who?

1136
01:18:05.921 --> 01:18:07.715
Major General Beaumont
calling from Halifax.

1137
01:18:07.716 --> 01:18:08.925
His plane's just been delayed.

1138
01:18:09.134 --> 01:18:10.134
Bad weather.

1139
01:18:10.594 --> 01:18:11.594
Yes?

1140
01:18:14.847 --> 01:18:16.515
Thank you. Beaumont.
I'll call you back.

1141
01:18:19.353 --> 01:18:20.770
Tomorrow's invasion is a slaughter.

1142
01:18:20.895 --> 01:18:22.904
I'm dead within five minutes
of landing on that beach.

1143
01:18:22.916 --> 01:18:24.935
along with every other
soldier you are sending.

1144
01:18:24.940 --> 01:18:27.319
And that's because
the enemy knows we're coming.

1145
01:18:27.735 --> 01:18:29.029
Now how do I know this?

1146
01:18:29.237 --> 01:18:30.738
Before I died I killed a Mimic.

1147
01:18:30.738 --> 01:18:31.859
only this one was different.

1148
01:18:32.114 --> 01:18:34.117
It passed something
onto me in my blood.

1149
01:18:34.242 --> 01:18:36.787
Now I relive the same day
over and over again.

1150
01:18:36.912 --> 01:18:38.204
Just like they do.

1151
01:18:38.329 --> 01:18:40.623
Just like Sergeant Vrataski at Verdun.

1152
01:18:41.041 --> 01:18:42.833
Tell your secretary everything's fine.

1153
01:18:43.918 --> 01:18:45.127
I beg your pardon?

1154
01:18:48.422 --> 01:18:50.591
Oh. I'm sorry. General.
I thought you were alone.

1155
01:18:50.716 --> 01:18:51.716
It's fine.

1156
01:18:51.842 --> 01:18:53.804
She typed up those orders
for you to authorize.

1157
01:18:53.929 --> 01:18:56.488
but she left out the word
eferring to the fuel duct in Greenwich.

1158
01:18:58.934 --> 01:18:59.934
Your name is Iris.

1159
01:19:00.143 --> 01:19:01.686
You're birthday is September 17th.

1160
01:19:02.729 --> 01:19:06.023
The General probably pulled some strings
stationed your only son in Australia.

1161
01:19:06.024 --> 01:19:07.734
as far from the war as possible.

1162
01:19:07.859 --> 01:19:10.658
Tell the General his dinner's been
canceled. the call came in just now.

1163
01:19:12.780 --> 01:19:14.365
Your dinner was canceled.

1164
01:19:14.949 --> 01:19:16.868
You forgot the fuel duct.

1165
01:19:17.703 --> 01:19:19.662
Thank you. Iris.
That will be all.

1166
01:19:27.462 --> 01:19:29.922
- Cage. Let's go.
- Rita.

1167
01:19:30.047 --> 01:19:31.528
- Let me just...
- What are you doing?

1168
01:19:31.550 --> 01:19:32.671
Please. don't shoot him yet.

1169
01:19:33.342 --> 01:19:34.720
Okay? Just...

1170
01:19:39.056 --> 01:19:40.056
General.

1171
01:19:40.057 --> 01:19:42.518
Th... this isn't the first time
we've had this conversation.

1172
01:19:42.519 --> 01:19:45.855
Cause that's... because you're...
you're stubborn.

1173
01:19:46.814 --> 01:19:49.567
You won't believe me when I tell you
that Dr. Carter was right.

1174
01:19:49.568 --> 01:19:52.487
That the enemy can manipulate time.

1175
01:19:52.695 --> 01:19:53.695
The invasion will fail.

1176
01:19:53.863 --> 01:19:56.408
no matter how many bodies you throw at it.

1177
01:19:56.574 --> 01:19:58.242
And the only way to win this war.

1178
01:19:58.243 --> 01:20:01.287
is by finding this power
source within the cord

1179
01:20:01.287 --> 01:20:02.204
and killing it.

1180
01:20:02.206 --> 01:20:04.166
And the only means of finding it

1181
01:20:04.332 --> 01:20:05.876
is in that safe right there.

1182
01:20:08.086 --> 01:20:10.421
No matter how many times
that we have this conversation.

1183
01:20:10.671 --> 01:20:13.759
you refuse to accept that the enemy
breaks through to London tomorrow.

1184
01:20:13.884 --> 01:20:15.135
and we lose.

1185
01:20:15.344 --> 01:20:16.345
We lose everything.

1186
01:20:24.435 --> 01:20:25.854
Let's say for the moment.

1187
01:20:27.271 --> 01:20:29.065
that I can't rationally explain...

1188
01:20:30.399 --> 01:20:32.277
your impressive parlor tricks.

1189
01:20:34.738 --> 01:20:36.782
Dr. Carter told me...

1190
01:20:37.448 --> 01:20:39.658
this device requires a live Mimic to work.

1191
01:20:39.868 --> 01:20:40.868
What use is it to you?

1192
01:20:41.953 --> 01:20:43.913
- That's my concern.
- On the contrary.

1193
01:20:44.331 --> 01:20:46.625
According to you. this
concerns the whole world.

1194
01:20:47.000 --> 01:20:49.961
Well what would you do if you believed
everything I just told you?

1195
01:20:51.755 --> 01:20:53.673
- I would locate this...
- Omega.

1196
01:20:53.798 --> 01:20:55.150
And bomb it out of existence.

1197
01:20:55.175 --> 01:20:57.110
You're not mentally equipped
to fight this thing.

1198
01:20:57.135 --> 01:20:58.177
and you never will be.

1199
01:21:15.779 --> 01:21:17.363
What do we do now?

1200
01:21:18.280 --> 01:21:19.990
I don't know.
We've never gotten this far.

1201
01:21:27.207 --> 01:21:28.266
That was easy.

1202
01:21:28.291 --> 01:21:29.583
Stop! Stop right there!

1203
01:21:29.792 --> 01:21:30.792
Don't move!

1204
01:21:30.918 --> 01:21:31.918
Nobody move!

1205
01:21:33.838 --> 01:21:34.838
Drop it!

1206
01:21:43.597 --> 01:21:44.681
How am I supposed to do this?

1207
01:21:44.682 --> 01:21:45.684
Stick it in your leg!

1208
01:21:46.350 --> 01:21:47.350
Do it!

1209
01:22:05.662 --> 01:22:06.954
Cage. what happened?

1210
01:22:08.164 --> 01:22:09.164
Talk to me!

1211
01:22:09.832 --> 01:22:12.252
I feel it. it... it's taking me there.

1212
01:22:13.002 --> 01:22:14.212
What do you see?

1213
01:22:16.131 --> 01:22:17.466
It's... it's the Louvre.

1214
01:22:17.591 --> 01:22:18.841
Where? Where else?

1215
01:22:19.509 --> 01:22:21.552
I'm inside now. It's flooded.

1216
01:22:22.762 --> 01:22:25.931
I'm going down a garage.
a garage underneath the museum.

1217
01:22:26.224 --> 01:22:27.684
<I<The Omega. do you see it?

1218
01:22:34.608 --> 01:22:35.609
It's in Paris!

1219
01:22:53.502 --> 01:22:54.502
Rita!

1220
01:23:36.002 --> 01:23:37.503
What have you done?

1221
01:23:38.046 --> 01:23:39.422
What have you done?

1222
01:23:41.925 --> 01:23:44.136
You'll be fine.
You just needed blood.

1223
01:23:44.720 --> 01:23:46.721
You don't know what you've just done.

1224
01:23:47.139 --> 01:23:48.724
I'm not allowed to talk to you.

1225
01:23:48.849 --> 01:23:50.307
I was with someone.

1226
01:23:52.269 --> 01:23:54.104
Rita Vrataski. Is she alive?

1227
01:23:54.813 --> 01:23:56.064
Rita Vrataski?

1228
01:23:56.731 --> 01:23:57.731
Please.

1229
01:23:58.608 --> 01:23:59.608
Just tell me that.

1230
01:24:02.404 --> 01:24:03.529
Please tell me.

1231
01:24:04.655 --> 01:24:05.655
I'm sorry.

1232
01:24:42.733 --> 01:24:44.984
I was out of those things in
three minutes flat. Cage.

1233
01:24:44.984 --> 01:24:45.984
What's wrong with you?

1234
01:24:47.695 --> 01:24:49.072
I thought you were dead.

1235
01:24:49.823 --> 01:24:50.823
Not yet.

1236
01:24:56.037 --> 01:24:57.037
I'm sorry. Cage.

1237
01:24:57.163 --> 01:24:58.181
No! Wait. wait. wait!

1238
01:24:58.206 --> 01:24:59.875
I'm out! I'm out!

1239
01:25:00.042 --> 01:25:01.042
They gave me blood!

1240
01:25:05.546 --> 01:25:06.590
I lost the power.

1241
01:25:08.884 --> 01:25:09.884
I feel it.

1242
01:25:11.136 --> 01:25:12.930
I can't reset the day anymore.

1243
01:25:28.153 --> 01:25:29.404
We have to kill the Omega.

1244
01:25:29.863 --> 01:25:31.448
before the invasion starts.

1245
01:25:32.490 --> 01:25:34.076
That gives us less than three hours.

1246
01:25:35.243 --> 01:25:37.703
We need a drop ship to
get to Paris in time.

1247
01:25:38.788 --> 01:25:40.289
We need more soldiers too.

1248
01:25:40.832 --> 01:25:43.001
No one's crazy enough
to follow us to Paris.

1249
01:25:50.132 --> 01:25:51.132
Cage!

1250
01:25:51.426 --> 01:25:52.426
Cage!

1251
01:25:52.426 --> 01:25:52.970
Guys!

1252
01:25:52.970 --> 01:25:53.845
We've been looking everywhere for you!

1253
01:25:54.470 --> 01:25:55.489
Just listen...

1254
01:25:55.514 --> 01:25:58.154
Farell almost strung us up by our bullocks
for losing track of you!

1255
01:25:58.266 --> 01:25:59.268
Just listen.

1256
01:25:59.643 --> 01:26:01.353
But you're gonna want to hear this story.

1257
01:26:01.478 --> 01:26:03.573
Now it's gonna sound
ridiculous at first. but the

1258
01:26:03.585 --> 01:26:05.690
longer I talk the more
rational it's going to appear.

1259
01:26:06.042 --> 01:26:07.042
Yeah?!

1260
01:26:07.067 --> 01:26:08.694
He named the school I went to.

1261
01:26:09.444 --> 01:26:12.072
and then he tells me
my second grade teacher

1262
01:26:12.280 --> 01:26:13.591
was called Miss Pollyhook.

1263
01:26:13.614 --> 01:26:16.135
She wouldn't let him go to the bathroom.
made his wet his pants.

1264
01:26:16.576 --> 01:26:17.576
Shut up!

1265
01:26:18.287 --> 01:26:21.456
Look. I'm telling you.
he know everything...

1266
01:26:22.332 --> 01:26:23.350
about all of us.

1267
01:26:23.375 --> 01:26:24.375
Bullshit.

1268
01:26:24.960 --> 01:26:26.020
Yeah?

1269
01:26:26.043 --> 01:26:28.296
He says your name ain't really Ford.

1270
01:26:29.131 --> 01:26:30.798
He says Ford was your friend.

1271
01:26:30.923 --> 01:26:32.717
died in combat on his first day.

1272
01:26:33.135 --> 01:26:35.679
You took his place.
send your checks to his family.

1273
01:26:36.012 --> 01:26:38.015
You slippery bitch.

1274
01:26:38.431 --> 01:26:40.141
Cage says the enemy knows us too.

1275
01:26:40.350 --> 01:26:41.851
They're waiting for us on the beach.

1276
01:26:42.101 --> 01:26:43.121
and we all die.

1277
01:26:43.145 --> 01:26:44.645
The whole invasion is a slaughter.

1278
01:27:01.855 --> 01:27:04.399
But it means coming with me. right now.

1279
01:27:04.818 --> 01:27:05.859
Listen. pal.

1280
01:27:06.069 --> 01:27:08.779
I don't really care
what you think you know about us.

1281
01:27:09.197 --> 01:27:10.405
We just met you.

1282
01:27:12.199 --> 01:27:14.327
Come on. why would we
follow him into combat?

1283
01:27:19.416 --> 01:27:20.917
I don't expect you to follow me.

1284
01:27:21.792 --> 01:27:23.293
I expect you to follow her.

1285
01:27:27.841 --> 01:27:29.966
That's the full metal bi...
J Squad.

1286
01:27:31.136 --> 01:27:32.386
This is Rita Vrataski.

1287
01:27:33.139 --> 01:27:35.180
Otherwise known as...
Yeah. yeah.

1288
01:27:36.056 --> 01:27:37.559
The Angel of Verdun.

1289
01:27:48.444 --> 01:27:49.570
Okay.

1290
01:27:59.079 --> 01:28:00.372
It's a new day. people!

1291
01:28:00.873 --> 01:28:02.000
Destiny calls.

1292
01:28:02.542 --> 01:28:04.877
The world expects only one thing from us:

1293
01:28:04.877 --> 01:28:05.920
That we will win!

1294
01:28:06.087 --> 01:28:08.046
Rest assured they enemy will thank you

1295
01:28:08.046 --> 01:28:09.757
for not giving a hundred percent today.

1296
01:28:10.132 --> 01:28:11.132
Squad!

1297
01:28:14.345 --> 01:28:15.471
Where's J Squad?

1298
01:28:34.033 --> 01:28:35.033
Right. okay.

1299
01:28:35.033 --> 01:28:37.577
So this Omega. it controls time?

1300
01:28:37.786 --> 01:28:40.037
Exploding it into pieces and sending
its bullocks back to where it came from!

1301
01:28:40.246 --> 01:28:41.247
And then we go home!

1302
01:28:42.247 --> 01:28:43.559
Right. it's guarded by an Alpha...

1303
01:28:43.582 --> 01:28:45.210
Just kill it. okay?

1304
01:28:45.752 --> 01:28:46.811
No!

1305
01:28:46.836 --> 01:28:48.480
You head what Cage said.

1306
01:28:48.505 --> 01:28:49.713
Do not kill an Alpha.

1307
01:28:49.922 --> 01:28:52.341
If we kill an Alpha. the Omega
will reset this whole day.

1308
01:28:53.342 --> 01:28:55.011
We'll never even remember
we had this conversation.

1309
01:28:55.302 --> 01:28:56.322
They're gonna know we're coming.

1310
01:28:56.345 --> 01:28:59.431
So what am I supposed to do if one of
those Alpha's is about to kill me?

1311
01:28:59.849 --> 01:29:01.059
Take a hit for the team.

1312
01:29:04.979 --> 01:29:06.189
When we're on the ground.

1313
01:29:06.648 --> 01:29:09.007
there's not gonna be much time
before they know we're there.

1314
01:29:10.819 --> 01:29:12.153
We're gonna need eyes up here.

1315
01:29:14.072 --> 01:29:15.323
I'm going in. Cage.

1316
01:29:26.876 --> 01:29:28.293
Thirty seconds. still contact.

1317
01:29:45.287 --> 01:29:46.287
Kimmel.

1318
